'Tightening the hell out of them' is wrong!
Get a torque wrench and torque them all to 94 ft-lbs.
The $10 one at Harbor Freight works very well for this, when it is on sale.
Normally it is $20. It seems to be 'on sale' every other week.
http://www.harborfreight.com/cpi/ctaf/Displayitem.taf?itemnumber=239
